GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Call for Papers for a Special Session on Intelligent Techniques for Mobile Multimedia Information Access First International Workshop on Intelligent Multimedia Computing and Networking ( IMMCN'2000 ) In conjunction with Fifth Joint Conference on Information Sciences Taj Mahal , Atlantic City , New Jersey , USA February 27 to March 3 , 2000 The proliferation of wireless networking and portable computing technologies have made feasible the idea of information access anywhere and anytime . However , current networking and information technologies still have significant obstacles to overcome before truly ubiquitous information access becomes a reality . In particular , mobile multimedia information access challenges the research community to provide more efficient and reliable techniques for effective data management and seamless data transfer under resource poor and constantly changing mobile environment . This special session provides a forum for academics and industrialists in both mobile and multimedia computing communities to exploit intelligent techniques for multimedia information access in mobile environment . Topics of interest include , but are not limited to : * Multimedia computing * Mobile multimedia data management * Mobile multimedia database access * Intelligent image search / retrieval techniques * Mobile access to audio / video information * Disconnected operations * Multimedia information broadcast * Mobile web browsing * Intelligent caching and prefetching for mobile environment * Intelligent techniques for adaptive mobile computing * Agent assisted mobile information access * Intelligent user interface * Personalized access to multimedia information * Mobile multimedia networking Paper submission Paper must be written in English . Please send four copies of your 4 - page extended summary ( 10 point , double column , and single-spaced ) and your full length double-spaced complete manuscript ( include figures and references ) to the session chair . The conference proceedings will publish the four pages of extended summary . Paper publication guideline should follow the one of IMMCN'2000 . Special Session Chair Dr .
